      "justification": "If confirmed, the central theorem has little empirical methodological value in its current form. The paper would need revision to either operationalize Z and specify estimation/testing procedures, or further downgrade claims from diagnostic framework to purely conditional formal observation. This weakens but does not necessarily nullify the paper."
    },
    {
      "finding": "The assumption S ⟂ T | (G,Z) is extremely strong and effectively removes the selector's possible information from X, even though S is explicitly defined as depending on (X,G). The paper states this is a modeling assumption, but many downstream interpretations treat it as plausibly characterizing self-evaluation without a method to verify it.",
