      "finding": "Several interpretive sections draw practical conclusions from literature that does not measure the manuscript's formal quantities. For example, the Self-Correction Blind Spot metric is repeatedly linked to false acceptance and shared-blind-spot structure despite explicit acknowledgment that the mapping is loose.",
      "severity": "MINOR",
      "justification": "If confirmed, this is mainly a claim-discipline/reporting issue. Tightening the wording and avoiding suggestive mapping would improve methodological correctness, but it does not break the formal results themselves."
    },
