      "finding": "The corollary 'External Selection Criterion' is labeled as a corollary but is not actually derived from prior formal results in a precise way; it is a heuristic summary combining assumption violation, blind-spot overlap, and low false acceptance.",
      "severity": "MINOR",
      "justification": "If confirmed, this is a presentation/formal-logic issue. It should be relabeled as an informal design principle rather than a corollary. This would not materially alter conclusions."
    },
    {
      "finding": "The manuscript invokes illustrative numerical evidence bounds (e.g., epsilon values and bit interpretations) without connecting them to realistic prior odds or decision thresholds, which may make the practical significance of those bits easy to misread.",
      "severity": "MINOR",
      "justification": "If confirmed, this is a standard interpretability concern. Clarifying that likelihood-ratio bits are not direct posterior probabilities would improve exposition but would not change the theorem."
    },
    {
      "finding": "There is a mismatch between the broad rhetoric of 'limits of self-correction in LLMs' and the actual conditional scope of the results. The body contains caveats, but the title, contribution framing, and some discussion sections still risk overgeneralization from a narrow formal regime.",
      "severity": "MINOR",
      "justification": "If confirmed, this is chiefly a framing issue. It warrants noting and revising language, but does not make the paper methodologically unsound on its own."
    }
  ]
}

